---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE_NAME } from '../consts';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description={`Privacy Policy for ${SITE_NAME}.`}
>
  <article class="article">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="article__meta" style="border: 0; padding: 0; margin-top: -0.25rem;">
      Last updated: July 20th, 2026
    </p>
    <div class="article__body">
      <p>
        This Privacy Policy explains how {SITE_NAME} (“we”, “us”) collects and
        uses information when you visit the Site.
      </p>

      <h2>Who we are</h2>
      <p>
        The Site is owned and operated by <strong>AK Ventures Inc.</strong>
      </p>

      <h2>Information we collect</h2>
      <h3>Analytics</h3>
      <p>
        We use <strong>Google Analytics</strong> (Google LLC) to understand how
        visitors use the Site. Google Analytics may collect information such as
        pages viewed, approximate location derived from IP address, device and
        browser type, and referral source. Google may process this data on our
        behalf under its own terms and privacy policy.
      </p>
      <p>
        In the European Union and Canada (including Québec), we load Google
        Analytics only if you accept analytics cookies in our cookie banner. You
        can also use Google’s Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on where available.
      </p>

      <h3>Email</h3>
      <p>
        If you subscribe to our email list, we collect the email address you
        submit (and any preferences the form asks for) so we can send travel
        news updates and manage the list. Signup and delivery are handled by{' '}
        <strong>Beehiiv</strong> (Beehiiv Inc.). Beehiiv processes subscriber
        data on our behalf. You can unsubscribe at any time using the link in
        our emails. For more detail, see Beehiiv’s privacy policy.
      </p>

      <h3>Server and security logs</h3>
      <p>
        Our hosting provider may automatically process technical logs (for
        example IP address, timestamps, and request URLs) needed to operate and
        secure the Site.
      </p>

      <h2>Cookies and similar technologies</h2>
      <p>
        We use cookies and similar technologies for:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Essential:</strong> remembering your cookie preference so we
          do not keep asking.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Analytics:</strong> Google Analytics, if you accept (required
          in the EU and Canada, including Québec, before we load it).
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        You can change your mind by clearing site data for this domain in your
        browser, which resets the banner, or by blocking cookies in your browser
        settings. See also our cookie banner when it appears.
      </p>

      <h2>How we use information</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>To measure and improve the Site</li>
        <li>To understand which stories attract readers</li>
        <li>To send email you asked for</li>
        <li>To maintain security and troubleshoot issues</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Sharing</h2>
      <p>
        We do not sell your personal information. We share data with service
        providers who help us run the Site — including Google (Analytics),
        Beehiiv (email), and our hosting provider — only as needed for those
        services.
      </p>

      <h2>Retention</h2>
      <p>
        Analytics data is retained according to our Google Analytics settings
        and Google’s policies. Email subscription data is kept until you
        unsubscribe or we close the list.
      </p>

      <h2>Your choices</h2>
      <p>
        Where the cookie banner applies, you can accept or reject analytics
        cookies. You can also block cookies in your browser, use Google’s
        opt-out tools where available, and unsubscribe from email using the link
        in any message we send.
      </p>

      <h2>Children</h2>
      <p>
        The Site is not directed at children under 13, and we do not knowingly
        collect personal information from them.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this policy from time to time. The “Last updated” date at
        the top will change when we do.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        For privacy questions, see our <a href="/contact/">Contact</a> page.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
